 Former Super Eagles target Bukayo Saka has won a double award after winning Arsenal’s player of the month and Goal of the month for December. The 19-year-old Nigerian descent has been one of the few shining lights in Arsenal’s underwhelming season so far and continued that form into the final month of 2020. Saka beat off competition from runner-up Kieran Tierney, and 3rd-placed Alexandre Lacazette to emerge the winner after he got 70% of the vote, according to Arsenal’s website. 🏆 𝗗𝗲𝗰𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝗣𝗹𝗮𝘆𝗲𝗿 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗠𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗵
🥇 @BukayoSaka87 Congratulations, Bukayo 👏 pic.twitter.com/1fCAGIrNr0 — Arsenal (@Arsenal) January 7, 2021 The former Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) target also emerge, winner for the Goal of the Month with his chipped over Eduardo Mendy in Arsenal 3-1 over Chelsea 26 of December. Saka beat off competition from Egyptian midfielder Mohammed Eleny and Switzerland skipper Granit Xhaka. 🏆 𝗗𝗲𝗰𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝗚𝗼𝗮𝗹 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗠𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗵 Our winner… 🥇 @BukayoSaka87 v Chelsea pic.twitter.com/7jtJ1cJGSd — Arsenal (@Arsenal) January 8, 2021 The Gunners will hope that the England international can continue to deliver these impressive performances for them well into the future. Their next game will be in the FA Cup against Newcastle United before they face Crystal Palace in the league. Post Views: 
